{
  "stem": "1338.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then my aunt, the one who you see the picture on that we used to go to the summer-- that we used to spend summers with, she got typhoid.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And after you recover from it, you have to eat a lot.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So her daughter, my favorite cousin, again, Lillian-- there is a picture of her there-- she decided to feed her mother her portion of bread without knowing-- letting her know.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, needless to say, after being completely without food for about two months, she developed, what is called, accelerated tuberculosis and burned up in about six weeks.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They didn't let me see her when she was sick.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so that took care of just about everybody.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The only people that disappeared from our lives as far as my extended family was concerned was the parents of my cousin in Warsaw now.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They moved to other city, Lvov, because he was, at that time, directing theatre there, and they disappeared, of course, perished there.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The others were-- I related how they disappeared, all of them, by May, 1943.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the only remaining extended family was my aunt with her older daughter.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she was herded into on a truck in August, 1944 during the liquidation and probably sent to Auschwitz, directly into the gas chamber.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So the only thing that were left was my mother and I.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was-- no, my aunt and her daughter stayed in Lodz Ghetto until the end in August, 1944.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, we lived in separate places.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had another room somewhere.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So now the first work I did was a friend of one of my classmates, the father had a-- was directing one of the plants, which happened to be later.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the whole class when there.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
